 observed behavior does NOT pose an imminent threat to safety, security or health, individuals are strongly encouraged to contact UIC Police:   312-355-5555 or 5-5555 from a campus phone  TDD: 312-413-9323  Non-Emergency: 312-996-2830  Information Line: 312-413-9696        Where to Receive Victim Assistance and Advocacy?     Confidential Resources         Confidential Resources   If you are a victim of violence and would like to confidentially talk with someone to review your on and off campus options and to put in place safety plans, you may contact the following offices:  UIC’s Campus Advocacy Network (CAN): 312-413-8206  Office for Access and Equity (OAE), Title IX Coordinator: 312-996-8670  Office of the Dean of Students: 312-996-4857  Student Counseling Center: 312-996-3490        Other Campus Resources         Other Campus Resources   UI Hospital Emergency Room: 312-996-7298        Community Resources         Community resources   Rape Victim Advocates: 312-443-9603  Chicago Rape Crisis Hotline: 888-293-2080  Chicago Domestic Violence Hotline: 877-863-6338  Illinois Attorney General – Helping Crime Victims            Safety on Campus        UIC SAFE  Tips & resources to staying safe on campus          Office of Preparedness & Response  UIC's safety toolkit              Assistance    Back to main content           Academic Concerns     Academic Resources    Academic Grievances    Withdrawal    Emergencies and Absences      Health & Personal Concerns     Hospitalization & Emergencies    Mental Health    Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns    Housing Instability & Food Insecurity    Financial Concerns    Cannabis: Know the Facts      Campus Life    Faculty & Staff Resources     The Student Response Team    Behavioral Response Intervention Team      U & I Care     Meet Our Partners    Care Facts    News & Events    U & I Care Fund    U & I Care Plan                    UIC Logo        Office of the Dean of Students         DOS Offices    Career Services    Student